  "street_address__contact_details.directions": {
    "answer": "From Highway 63, take the Route B exit toward Hallsville and continue east for approximately 6 miles. Turn left (north) onto Route J. Continue on Route J for about 2.3 miles; the property is on the right (east) side of the road just past the small concrete bridge over the creek. White single-story farmhouse with a green metal roof, gravel driveway, and a red mailbox marked \"8427\". The flight pens and small barn with metal siding are located behind the house; please follow the driveway all the way back to the barn area for wildlife enclosures and holding pens.",
